The Herald Runesu Gwidi in MASVINGO Police in Masvingo have arrested a notorious jailbird, Tafadzwa Kanengoni, infamously known as “Soda Water”, for the suspected murder of well-known tuckshop owner, Michael Munhungowarwa. The businessman was killed at Sisk business centre recently. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-665114 size-medium" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2023/01/rdbfh-360x201.jpg" alt="" width="360" height="201" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2023/01/rdbfh-360x200.jpg 360w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2023/01/rdbfh.jpg 680w" sizes="(max-width: 360px) 100vw, 360px" /> Scores of residents followed events as Criminal Investigation Department detectives took Kanengoni to the station. <img class="size-medium wp-image-665116 aligncenter" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2023/01/Untitled-33.eaasd_-360x201.jpg" alt="" width="360" height="201" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2023/01/Untitled-33.eaasd_-360x200.jpg 360w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2023/01/Untitled-33.eaasd_.jpg 680w" sizes="(max-width: 360px) 100vw, 360px" /> Masvingo provincial police spokesperson, Inspector Kudakwashe Dehwa said investigations were in progress and full details would be given later.